  "body": "When compiling with hardhat it uses `config.paths.root` as the root of the source code this adds an extra `contracts/` to the source of the contracts (even if `config.paths.sources` is set to `contracts`). Is seems that this problem can be fixed by using `config.paths.sources` instead of `config.paths.root` in the following tasks:\r\n\r\n- [TASK_COMPILE_SOLIDITY_GET_SOURCE_NAMES](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/2295c04c8fb598932023193ca411307013d44712/packages/hardhat-core/src/builtin-tasks/compile.ts#L144)\r\n\r\n- [TASK_COMPILE_SOLIDITY_GET_DEPENDENCY_GRAPH](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/2295c04c8fb598932023193ca411307013d44712/packages/hardhat-core/src/builtin-tasks/compile.ts#L193)\r\n\r\nThis affects the compilation metadata and then the ipfs hash in the bytecode so this change can be problematic, in any case it seems that there is a bug and using  `config.paths.sources`  is the right thing to do. ",
